<inglise> Council Directive 86/467/EEC of 14 July 1986 concerning the Community list of less-favoured farming areas within the meaning of Directive 75/268/EEC (Portugal) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 86/467/EM&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse loetelu &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade kohta direktiivis 75/268/EM&Uuml; m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses (Portugal) 14. juuli 1986 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 75/268/EEC of 28 April 1975 on mountain and hill farming and farming in certain less-favoured areas (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 797/85 (2), and in particular Article 2 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 28. aprilli 1975. aasta direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; m&auml;gipiirkondade ja teatavate ebasoodsamate alade p&otilde;llumajanduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 797/85, (2) eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Government of the Republic of Portugal has communicated to the Commission, pursuant to Article 2 (1) of Directive 75/268/EEC, areas suitable for inclusion in the Community list of less-favoured farming areas as well as information relating to the characteristics of these areas; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Portugali Vabariigi valitsus on vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 1 teatanud komisjonile &uuml;henduse v&auml;hemsoodsate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade loetellu lisamiseks sobivad alad ning nende alade tunnuseid k&auml;sitleva teabe; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the following criteria were used to define mountain areas according to Article 3 (3) of Directive 75/268/EEC: in the area north of the Tagus a minimum altitude of 700 metres, in the area south of the Tagus a minimum altitude of 800 metres; or where slope is concerned a slope of greater than 25 %; whereas where there is a combination of the factors altitude and slope, mountain areas within the meaning of Article 3 (3) of Directive 75/268/EEC may be defined by: between 400 and 700 metres altitude and a slope of at least 20 % in the area north of the Tagus, and by between 600 and 800 metres of altitude with a slope of at least 15 % in the area south of the Tagus; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;gipiirkondade m&auml;&auml;ratlemiseks vastavalt direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 3 on kasutatud j&auml;rgmisi kriteeriume: Tejo j&otilde;est p&otilde;hja pool asuva piirkonna puhul miinimumk&otilde;rgus 700 meetrit, Tejo j&otilde;est l&otilde;una pool asuva piirkonna puhul miinimumk&otilde;rgus 800 meetrit; n&otilde;lva puhul kalle &uuml;le 25%line; juhul, kui on tegu k&otilde;rguse ja n&otilde;lva kombinatsiooniga, v&otilde;ib m&auml;gipiirkondi direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses m&auml;&auml;ratleda j&auml;rgmiselt: Tejo j&otilde;est p&otilde;hja pool asuva piirkonna puhul k&otilde;rgus 400-700 meetrini ja kalle v&auml;hemalt 20%, Tejo j&otilde;est l&otilde;una pool asuva piirkonna puhul k&otilde;rgus 600-800 meetrini ja kalle v&auml;hemalt 15%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the presence of infertile land as referred to in Article 3 (4) (a) of Directive 75/268/EEC has been characterized by the existence of soil with accentuated limitations occupying at least 50 % of the utilized agricultural area of the Concelho; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 4 punktis a osutatud viljatut maad iseloomustab madala viljakusega mullastik, mis moodustab concelho p&otilde;llumajandusk&otilde;lvikust v&auml;hemalt 50%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the economic results of farming appreciably lower than the mean, as referred to in Article 3 (4) (b) of Directive 75/268/EEC are calculated using indices relating to a livestock density below 0,2 livestock unit per hectare forage area in the Concelho or in the region; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 4 punktis b osutatud keskmisest tunduvalt madalamad p&otilde;llumajanduse majandustulemused on arvutatud n&auml;itude p&otilde;hjal, mille j&auml;rgi loomkoormus on alla 0,2 loom&uuml;hiku s&ouml;&ouml;damaa hektari kohta concelho's v&otilde;i piirkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the following indices have been utilized in respect of low or dwindling population as predominantly dependent on agricultural activity within the meaning of Article 3 (4) (c) of Directive 75/268/EEC: population density of less than 56 persons per square kilometre (national average 111) or an annual regression in the population of more than 0,5 %, and at least 30 % of the working population engaged in agriculture; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 4 punktis c osutatud peamiselt p&otilde;llumajandusest s&otilde;ltuva v&auml;ikesearvulise v&otilde;i kahaneva elanikkonna suhtes on kasutatud j&auml;rgmisi n&auml;itajaid: rahvastikutihedus alla 56 inimese ruutkilomeetri kohta (riigi keskmine 111) v&otilde;i rahvaarvu aastane v&auml;henemine &uuml;le 0,5%, ning p&otilde;llumajandusega tegeleva t&ouml;&ouml;tava elanikkonna osa v&auml;hemalt 30%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, concerning the delimitation of areas affected by specific handicaps which can be considered as less-favoured areas within the meaning of Article 3 (5) of Directive 75/268/EEC, the following criteria have been used: isolation giving rise to heavy transport costs both from the mainland and between individual islands and lack of unity in the small local markets; in the Azores more than 50 % of the islands above 300 metres, and fragmented relief, strong winds, high humidity but lack of water retention; in Porto Santo, soil salinity, very low rainfall (less than 380 mm per year), lack of water reserves which together with the broken relief leads to soil erosion problems; on the mainland calcareous soils associated with very rocky outcrops; whereas moreover their combined area does not exceed 4,0 % of the area of this Member State (3,91 %); </inglise>
<eesti> selliste piirkondade piiritlemiseks, mida m&otilde;jutavad erilised ebasoodsad looduslikud tingimused ning mida v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitada ebasoodsamate piirkondadena direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 5 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses, on kasutatud j&auml;rgmisi kriteeriume: eraldatus, millest tingituna on transpordikulud suured nii mandriosalt kui &uuml;ksikute saarte vahel ning puudub &uuml;htsus v&auml;ikestel kohalikel turgudel; Assooridel rohkem kui 50% saarte paiknemine k&otilde;rgemal kui 300 meetrit, katkendlik pinnamood, tugevad tuuled, k&otilde;rge niiskus, kuid suur pinnase veel&auml;bilaskvus; Porto Santol mulla soolsus, v&auml;ga v&auml;he sademeid (alla 380 mm aastas) ja veevarude v&auml;hesus, mis koos katkendliku pinnamoega p&otilde;hjustab pinnaerosiooni; mandriosal lubjarikkad mullad kivistel paljanditel; lisaks sellele on nende piirkondade kogupindala alla 4,0% k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi pindalast (3,91%); </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the nature and level of the abovementioned indices used by the Government of the Portuguese Republic to define the three types of areas communicated to the Commission correspond respectively to the characteristics of the mountain areas, the less-favoured areas and the areas affected by specific handicaps referred to in Article 3 (3), (4) and (5) of Directive 75/268/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjonile edastatud alade t&uuml;&uuml;bi m&auml;&auml;ratlemiseks Portugali Vabariigi valitsuse poolt kasutatud ja eespool nimetatud n&auml;itajate laad ja tase vastavad direktiivi 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;igetes 3, 4 ja 5 esitatud m&auml;gipiirkondade, ebasoodsamate piirkodade ja erilistest ebasoodsatest looduslikest tingimustest m&otilde;jutatud piirkondade omadustele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Government of the Portuguese Republic has provided information on the public infrastructure available in these areas; whereas in general this infrastructure is deficient; whereas the Community is helping to tackle the priority problems under Regulation (EEC) No 3828/85 of 20 December 1985 on a specific programme for the development of Portuguese agriculture (4) and it therefore seems expedient to include the areas in question in the Community list of less-favoured farming areas, </inglise>
<eesti> Portugali Vabariigi valitsus on esitanud teabe k&otilde;nealuste alade avaliku infrastruktuuri kohta; &uuml;ldiselt on k&otilde;nealune infrastruktuur puudulik; &uuml;hendus toetab esmat&auml;htsate probleemide lahendamist vastavalt 20. detsembri 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 3828/85 Portugali p&otilde;llumajanduse arendamise erikava kohta (4) ning seet&otilde;ttu oleks otstarbekas lisada k&otilde;nealused piirkonnad &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade loetellu; </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The areas of Portugal listed in the Annex hereto shall be included in the Community list of less-favoured agricultural areas within the meaning of Article 3 (3), (4) and (5) of Directive 75/268/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi lisas osutatud Portugali alad lisatakse &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamate p&otilde;llumajanduspiirkondade loetellu direktiivi nr 75/268/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 l&otilde;igete 3, 4 ja 5 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Portuguese Republic. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud Portugali Vabariigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 14 July 1986. </inglise>
